# Sample .stconfig — copy this file to the TOP LEVEL of your --source project
# folder (the same place a .stignore file lives) and rename it to ".stconfig".
# Prefer a different location instead? Pass --config <path> to look there
# instead of --source. Neither given? Falls back to the current directory.
# See "Default options (.stconfig)" in README.md for the full rules.
#
# One "key=value" per line. Blank lines and lines starting with "#" are
# skipped. An explicit command-line flag always overrides the matching key
# here — this file only fills in what you didn't type.

# --- Paths & project name (mirror --source/--dest/--name) ---
# "source" only matters if this file is discovered somewhere OTHER than the
# source folder itself (i.e. via --config <path>) — if it lives at the top
# level of --source, as recommended, you're already there and can drop it.
# source=C:\path\to\ST\Shark
dest=C:\path\to\TwinCAT-projects-root
name=Shark

# --- Booleans: "true", "1", or "yes" (case-insensitive) are truthy; anything
# else, including a missing key, is false ---
incremental=true
# parse-only=true
# format-check=true
# check-events=true
# check-links=true

# --- Stage flags (sync-code, sync-libs, sync-io, sync-events, build) ---
# These five are a GROUP: if the command line names ANY --sync-*/--build
# flag, this whole group is ignored for that run — a config default here
# can never silently add an extra stage on top of a one-off CLI invocation.
# Uncomment to make a bare invocation (no stage flags) do a full run:
# sync-code=true
# sync-libs=true
# sync-io=true
# sync-events=true
# build=true

# --- Misc ---
# export=FB_Motor

# --- NEVER read from this file, no matter what ---
# --init, --confirm-delete, and --confirm-delete-io are safety-gated flags
# that must stay CLI-only, always — RunOptions.Parse never even attempts to
# read them from here. Listing them below would do nothing.
